{"article_id":"94faYA5QyMekwTaC","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Mr. Obama refuses to propose more spending cuts","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"until Republicans accept higher tax rates on the wealthy ,","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"and Republicans refuse to accept higher tax rates on the wealthy","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"while asking for more spending cuts .","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"\" I ' m puzzled","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"why Republicans are locking into a principle","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"that ' s not sustainable","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"and why Democrats aren ' t taking the moment","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"to put forward their own vision of entitlement reform , \"","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"said Peter R. Orszag , a former White House budget director for Mr. Obama .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"Mr. Orszag ' s former White House colleagues said","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"they had grown tired of making unilateral concessions","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"only to see Republicans moving the goal posts ,","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"as they see it .","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"\" The president is not going to negotiate with himself , \"","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"said Dan Pfeiffer , the White House communications director .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"\" He ' s laid out his position ,","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"and Republicans have to come to the table . \"","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"Republican strategists argue","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"in resorting to campaign-style events","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"to take his fiscal message to voters ,","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"Mr. Obama is overplaying his hand ,","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"much as President George W. Bush did after his re-election","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"when he barnstormed the country in favor of a Social Security restructuring plan","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"that he never successfully sold to leaders on Capitol Hill .","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"\" He is overreading his mandate , \"","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"said John Feehery , a former adviser to top House Republicans .","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"\" By doing the campaign thing ,","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"he is making the same mistake","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"Bush made in 2005. \"","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"Eventually ,","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"he said ,","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"Democratic and Republican leaders \" are going to cut the deal ,","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"and Obama is going to be on the outside","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"looking in . \"","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"The difference might be that Mr. Obama ran more explicitly on the idea","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"of letting Mr. Bush ' s tax cuts expire for incomes over $ 250,000 ,","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"while Mr. Bush ' s re-election was fought more on grounds of national security than Social Security .","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"But both presidents emerged from relatively narrow popular-vote victories","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"determined to impose their will on a balky Congress","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"resisting their leadership .","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"Mr. Obama seemed to defy the Republican House last week","depth":5},{"id":43,"text":"when Treasury Secretary Timothy F. Geithner delivered a plan","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"calling for $ 1.6 trillion in additional taxes from the wealthy over 10 years , as well as $ 50 billion in short-term stimulus spending and $ 612 billion in recycled cuts","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"first put on the table during last year ' s failed debt talks .","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"Republicans erupted in outrage ,","depth":6},{"id":47,"text":"though they produced no specific alternative .","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"Instead , they noted","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"they had expressed newfound willingness since the election","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"to increase tax revenue","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"by limiting deductions for the wealthy ,","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"though not by raising rates .","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"The administration laid out its latest plan in less formal ways a couple of weeks earlier ,","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"according to a senior official","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"who declined to be identified","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"discussing private deliberations .","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"But the message was that Speaker John A. Boehner could not move yet .","depth":5},{"id":58,"text":"After waiting with no further response ,","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"the administration decided to have Mr. Geithner deliver the proposal on paper","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"knowing","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"it would be provocative","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"but thinking","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"it was needed","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"to move the process along .","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"Instead , the process has collapsed , at least for now .","depth":5},{"id":66,"text":"The depth of disagreement played out on the Sunday morning talk shows ,","depth":6},{"id":67,"text":"even as Mr. Obama went golfing with former President Bill Clinton in a session","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"White House officials presumed","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"would include trading notes about the fiscal crisis .","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"\" We ' ve put a serious offer on the table","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"by putting revenues up there","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"to try to get this question resolved , \"","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"Mr. Boehner said on \" Fox News Sunday. \"","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"\" But the White House has responded with virtually nothing .","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"They have actually asked for more revenue","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"than they ' ve been asking for the whole entire time . \"","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"Mr. Geithner said","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"it was up to Republicans to outline more spending cuts","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"than Mr. Obama had previously put on the table .","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"\" Some Republicans apparently want to go beyond that ,","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"but what they have to do is tell us what they ' re prepared to do , \"","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"Mr. Geithner told Bob Schieffer on \" Face the Nation \" on CBS .","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"\" And what we can ' t do , Bob , is sit here","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"trying to guess what works for them . \"","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"Newsletter Sign Up","depth":4},{"id":87,"text":"Continue reading the main story","depth":4},{"id":88,"text":"Please verify","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"you 're not a robot","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"by clicking the box .","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"Invalid email address .","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"Please re-enter .","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"You must select a newsletter","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"to subscribe to .","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"Sign Up","depth":6},{"id":96,"text":"You will receive emails","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"containing news content , updates and promotions from The New York Times .","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"You may opt-out at any time .","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"You agree to receive occasional updates and special offers for The New York Times 's products and services .","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"Thank you for subscribing .","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"An error has occurred .","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"Please try again later .","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"View all New York Times newsletters .","depth":4},{"id":104,"text":"That represents something of a shift for Mr. Obama ,","depth":5},{"id":105,"text":"who did try to guess what worked for Republicans in his first term .","depth":5},{"id":106,"text":"When he crafted a stimulus spending program","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"to bolster the economy","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"shortly after taking office ,","depth":7},{"id":109,"text":"Mr. Obama devoted roughly a third of the money to tax cuts","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"he assumed","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"Republicans would like .","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"They did not .","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"Likewise , his framework for universal health care included free-market elements","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"he thought","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"Republicans would embrace .","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"They did not .","depth":6},{"id":119,"text":"While Republicans argued","depth":6},{"id":120,"text":"that the overall programs overshadowed any palatable aspects ,","depth":6},{"id":121,"text":"Mr. Obama came to believe","depth":7},{"id":122,"text":"he had made a mistake","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"in offering concessions up front .","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"In an interview in September 2010 , he said","depth":7},{"id":125,"text":"he had learned","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"\" that","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"if you already have a third of the package as tax cuts ,","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"then the Republicans ,","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"who traditionally are more comfortable with tax cuts ,","depth":13},{"id":130,"text":"may just pocket that","depth":12},{"id":131,"text":"and attack the other components of the program . \"","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"Aides said","depth":7},{"id":133,"text":"Mr. Obama came to the same conclusion","depth":8},{"id":134,"text":"after his clash with Republicans","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"over raising the nation ' s borrowing limit last year .","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"\" We put all these things on the table ,","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"and the reason","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"we couldn ' t do a deal","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"is because Republicans couldn ' t do revenues , \"","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"Mr. Pfeiffer said .","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"\" So our view here is the president won ' t sign a deal","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"that doesn ' t have higher rates for the wealthy .","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"Until they cross that bridge ,","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"nothing else is relevant . \"","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"Yet there is risk in that .","depth":6},{"id":146,"text":"Republicans now understand","depth":10},{"id":147,"text":"that higher tax rates on the wealthy is Mr. Obama ' s No . 1 priority ,","depth":10},{"id":148,"text":"so","depth":12},{"id":149,"text":"rather than give in ,","depth":12},{"id":150,"text":"some strategists say","depth":11},{"id":151,"text":"they should hold out","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"to leverage those","depth":12},{"id":153,"text":"to shape other aspects of a final deal .","depth":12},{"id":154,"text":"\" He only cares about one detail :","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"raising rates on the top two brackets , \"","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"said Tony Fratto , a former White House and Treasury Department official under Mr. Bush .","depth":11},{"id":157,"text":"\" Everything else is secondary .","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"That ' s why","depth":10},{"id":159,"text":"if that is going to happen ,","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"it will be last","depth":12},{"id":161,"text":"if Republicans can hold out .","depth":12},{"id":162,"text":"I think","depth":8},{"id":163,"text":"it ' s pretty clear Obama will sacrifice just about anything","depth":10},{"id":164,"text":"to get that .","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"It ' s the only win for him . \"","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":331,"left":251,"right":330,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":251,"left":218,"right":250,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":218,"left":207,"right":217,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":207,"left":183,"right":206,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":183,"left":169,"right":182,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":169,